        public MetricItems getBaseMetricList(java.lang.String application)

        This will return the list of the metric base paths available for example:

        • metric-items
          • metric-item
            • name = Business Transaction Performance
            • type = folder
          • metric-item
            • name = Mobile
            • type = folder
          • metric-item
            • name = Overall Application Performance
            • type = folder

            • name = Service End Points
            • type = folder
          • metric-item
            • name = End User Experience
            • type = folder
          • metric-item
            • name = Backends
            • type = folder
          • metric-item
            • name = Information Points
            • type = folder
          • metric-item
            • name = Errors
            • type = folder
          • metric-item
            • name = Application Infrastructure Performance
            • type = folder

        These paths can then be used to traverse custom metrics paths with AppDynamics.

        Parameters:
        application - Name of the application
        Returns:
        MetricItems

      • getBaseMetricListPath

        public MetricItems getBaseMetricListPath(java.lang.String application,
                                java.lang.String metricPath)

        This will allow the user to provide the metric path they wish to walk. The metricPaths parameter is the metric path and needs to be separated by the character '|'.

        • metric-items
          • metric-item
            • name = Business Transactions
            • type = folder
          • metric-item
            • name = Business Transaction Groups
            • type = folder
        *

        As long as the metric-item type is "folder" you can add it to the path of the metric path separated by '|'. Once you reach the type "leaf" you can request the metric using getBaseMetricListPath

        • metric-item
          • name = Average CPU Used (ms)
          • type = leaf
        Parameters:
        application - Name of the application
        metricPath - Metric path to the metric list requested
        Returns:
        MetricItems
